### [Joshua Chapter 18](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#001.md)

[Joshua](../../../bib/kjv/jos001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">jos 18:0</span></span>

Overview

[Jos 18:1](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#001.md), The tabernacle is set up at
Shiloh; [Jos 18:2](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#002.md), The remainder of
the land is described, and divided into seven parts; [Jos
18:10](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#010.md), Joshua distributes it by lot;
[Jos 18:11](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#011.md), The lot and border of
Benjamin; [Jos 18:21](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#021.md), Their cities.

[Joshua 18:1](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">jos 18:1</span></span>

Shiloh: Shiloh was situated on a hill in the tribe of Ephraim, though
near the borders of Benjamin, about fifteen miles north of Jerusalem,
and, according to Eusebius, twelve, or according to Jerome, ten miles
(south) from Shechem or Nablous. It was but a little north from Bethel
or Ai, and near the road from Shechem to Jerusalem ([Jdg
21:19](../../../bib/kjv/jdg021.htm#019).md). In Jerome's time, Shiloh was
ruined; and nothing remarkable was extant, but the foundations of the
altar of burnt offerings which had been erected when the tabernacle
stood there. [Jos 19:51](../../../bib/kjv/jos019.htm#051.md), [Jos
21:2](../../../bib/kjv/jos021.htm#002.md), [Jos
