[Joshua 18:9](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">jos 18:9</span></span>

described: The surveyors seem to have formed some kind of map of the
country, as well as a description of it in writing. The Egyptians, from
the situation of their fields, as annually overflowed by the Nile,
acquired great skill in mensuration and land surveying; and some of the
Israelites had, no doubt, learned these from them, without a knowledge
of which they could not properly have divided the land. This is probably
the first act of surveying on record.

